## Description
Our assigned disability is muscular dystrophy, a condition that causes progressive muscle weakness and makes movement harder over time. The game we created called Let Me Out, is a sliding block puzzle where players move the yellow target block to the exit on the right side of the grid by sliding other blocks out of the way. Each block can only move in one direction based on its orientation, so players must carefully plan their moves. As levels progress, puzzles become more constrained and blocks move slightly slower. This reflects the increasing physical effort associated with muscular dystrophy, encouraging players to slow down, plan ahead, and put more effort into completing the same task.
---
## Learning Goals

- Understand how sliding block puzzle mechanics and movement constraints influence problem solving
- Practice implementing grid-based movement where blocks move only in one direction based on orientation
- Learn how increasing level constraints and slower movement can raise game difficulty
- Explore how game mechanics can simulate the growing effort required for movement in muscular dystrophy

